Now, let us go to the lesson.
today's topic is d1, the last choice of 4th move
It is something that puzzled lots of top players in the world.
There were times when Kawamura (9dan) from Japan used it frequently in high level games.
And his opponents failed to win.
Is here anyone who knows black win?
Let us begin with checking the famous Kawamura's trap.
The theory focused on lower 4th move at that time.
This is quite clear so far.
Move 9 created many lines with controls,
and white used its open lines to block some of the black powers.
Move 16-e8 is also mentioned in theory.
Move 19 is not a VCF threat, but still controls everything.
Kawamura's trap is related to the board edge.
And it became clear, not enough space.
And black is in big big trouble.
This trap puzzled the minds of top players for years.
none of the books in world showed what to do,
and today, most top players still do not know the answer.
But today, you will know the answers.
To win here, black had to rebuild the whole concept.
But until recently, there was no ideas how to do.
two years ago, I played a similar game with RT on playsite. And I lost as black :-(
Move 8-f20 is considered to be weak.
and finally enjoy the lower space.
